JOHANNESBURG &#8211; Standard &amp; Poor&#8217;s decision to downgrade South Africa&#8217;s credit rating to below investment grade was a result of President Jacob Zuma&#8217;s &#8220;illogical and damaging&#8221; cabinet reshuffle, the Chamber of Mines, an industry lobby group, said on Tuesday.S&amp;P cut South Africa&#8217;s credit rating to junk status on Monday, saying the dismissal by Zuma of a respected finance minister heralded a damaging policy shift. 